From f1081d7f204f6672569dbd781eb3cb0446f9e004 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mo Badwy <badwy.mt@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 07:30:17 -0700
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] Fix registration hang + service worker API caching
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- users.ts: use admin.createUser() when DEV_BYPASS_OTP=true to bypass
  Supabase phone confirmation SMS (which was hanging the /register route
  indefinitely). Also use admin client for all DB inserts during
  registration to avoid RLS issues on fresh accounts.
- admin.ts: add 'user-registration' to allowed admin scopes
- next.config.js: change /api/* and supabase SW handler to NetworkOnly
  — prevents service worker from intercepting or caching API calls
- vercel.json: set DEV_BYPASS_OTP=true so testing env is active on Vercel

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
